<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 93/75/EEC of 13 September 1993 concerning minimum requirements for vessels bound for or leaving Community ports and carrying dangerous or polluting goods, and in particular Article 5 (4) thereof (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 13. septembri 1993. aasta direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; miinimumn&otilde;uete kohta, mis k&auml;sitlevad ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu vedavaid laevu, mis suunduvad &uuml;henduse sadamatesse v&otilde;i lahkuvad sealt, eriti selle artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 4, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to limit the risks of serious accidents at sea and to reduce the resulting damage, Article 5 of Directive 93/75/EEC provides that the operators of the vessels covered by the Directive shall notify the information listed in Annex I to the said Directive to the competent authorities of the Member State concerned; whereas Article 5 (4) authorizes the Member States to exempt regular scheduled services of less than one hour's crossing time from that notification requirement and allows the Commission to agree to a reasonable extension of this period at the request of a Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: v&auml;hendamaks t&otilde;siste &otilde;nnestuste ohtu merel ning sellest tulenevat kahju on direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artiklis 5 s&auml;testatud, et direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud laevade kasutajad esitavad nimetatud direktiivi I lisas loetletud teabe asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele; artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 4 lubatakse liikmesriikidel vabastada sellest teatamisn&otilde;udest alla tunnise &uuml;les&otilde;iduajaga regulaarliinid ning v&otilde;imaldatakse komisjonil n&otilde;ustuda liikmesriigi taotlusel selle aja m&otilde;istliku pikendamisega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in a request submitted on 12 July 1995 and amended by letter dated 29 March 1996, France asked the Commission to agree to an extension of this period for the scheduled services between Brest and Le Conquet (crossing time: 2 hours) and between Le Coquet and Ouessant (crossing time: 2 hours 30 minutes); </inglise>
<eesti> 12. juulil 1995 esitatud taotluses, mida muudeti 29. m&auml;rtsi 1996 kirjaga, palus Prantsusmaa komisjonil pikendada Bresti ja Le Conquet' (&uuml;les&otilde;iduaeg 2 tundi) ning Le Coquet' ja Quessant'i (&uuml;les&otilde;iduaeg 2 tundi ja 30 minutit) regulaarliinide puhul nimetatud aega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the ecological importance and hazards to shipping of the area concerned have led the French authorities to take appropriate measures to ensure a high level of safety for shipping in that area; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse piirkonna &ouml;koloogilise t&auml;htsuse ja meres&otilde;idu ohtlikkuse t&otilde;ttu on Prantsusmaa ametiasutused v&otilde;tnud kohased meetmed meres&otilde;iduohutuse k&otilde;rge taseme tagamiseks selles piirkonnas; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures consist of the buoyage of the area and information to sailors by means of appropriate nautical documentation; whereas in addition the Corsen-Ouessant maritime traffic service provides continuous surveillance of shipping in the area by radar and regular radio broadcasts of nautical information for sailors; </inglise>
<eesti> meetmete hulka kuulub piirkonna poidega m&auml;rgistamine ja kohase meredokumentide abil meres&otilde;itjate teavitamine; lisaks sellele tegeleb Corseni-Ouessant'i mereliiklustalitus k&otilde;nealuse piirkonna laevaliikluse pideva j&auml;relevalvega radarite abil ning esitab meres&otilde;itjatele regulaarsetes raadiosaadetes meres&otilde;iduinfot; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the risk of accident is limited owing to the scarce maritime traffic in the area and measures have been taken to keep vessels carrying dangerous or polluting cargoes away from the coastal navigation area; </inglise>
<eesti> &otilde;nnetuste oht on v&auml;ike, sest selles piirkonnas ei ole laevaliiklus tihe, samuti on v&otilde;etud meetmeid, et hoida ohtliku v&otilde;i saastava lastiga laevu eemal rannikualast; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the service in question provides local services between the islands and the mainland; whereas the quantities of pollutant goods on board are small; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealune liin on kohalik liin saarte ja mandri vahel; laeval olevate saastavate kaupade kogused on v&auml;ikesed; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the information required by Annex I to the Directive is available at any time from the operators or captains; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi I lisas n&otilde;utud teave on kasutajalt v&otilde;i kaptenitelt igal ajal k&auml;ttesaadav; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the circumstances, it is justified to accept France's request for exemption of the scheduled services referred to above from the application of Article 5 (2) and (3) of Directive 93/75/EEC, </inglise>
<eesti> antud asjaoludel on n&otilde;ustumine Prantsusmaa taotlusega vabastada eespool nimetatud regulaarliinid direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaldamisest p&otilde;hjendatud, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> France is hereby authorized to exempt the scheduled services between Brest and Le Conquet and between Le Conquet and Ouessant from the application of Article 5 (2) and (3) of Directive 93/75/EEC, subject to the following conditions: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga lubatakse Prantsusmaal vabastada Bresti ja Le Conquet' ning Le Conquet' ja Ouessant'i vahelised regulaarliinid direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaldamisest j&auml;rgmistel tingimustel: </eesti>
<inglise> - the waters in which the services covered by this Decision operate are duly buoyed and are drawn to the attention of sailors in appropriate nautical documents, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&auml;esoleva otsusega h&otilde;lmatud liiklus toimub vetes, mis on kohaselt poidega m&auml;rgistatud ning meres&otilde;itjate t&auml;helepanu juhitakse sellele kohastes meredokumentides, </eesti>
<inglise> - compliance with the local navigation rules is assured, </inglise>
<eesti> - tagatakse kohalike meres&otilde;idureeglite t&auml;itmine, </eesti>
<inglise> - constant contact is maintained, in particular by radio links, with the competent maritime traffic service, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&auml;deva mereliiklustalitusega ollakse pidevas &uuml;henduses, eriti raadioside kaudu, </eesti>
<inglise> - only small quantities of dangerous or polluting goods, within the meaning of Directive 93/75/EEC, are carried on board, </inglise>
<eesti> - laeval veetakse ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu ainult v&auml;ikeses koguses direktiivi 93//5EM&Uuml; t&auml;henduses, </eesti>
<inglise> - the information referred to in Annex I to Directive 93/75/EEC is available from the operators and captains throughout the crossing and can at any time be provided to the authorities of the Member State on request. </inglise>
<eesti> - direktiivi 93//5/EM&Uuml; I lisas osutatud teave on kasutajalt ja kaptenitelt k&auml;ttesaadav kogu &uuml;les&otilde;idu jooksul ning taotluse korral saab seda igal ajal esitada liikmesriigi ametiasutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the French Republic. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud Prantsuse Vabariigile. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 29 July 1996. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 29. juuli 1996 </eesti>
